112
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:26,760
{\an5}The less they know
what's going on, the better.

113
00:06:26,840 --> 00:06:29,920
{\an5}You sure you want to leave
daddy's little girl with that punk?

114
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:32,920
{\an5}Even before the League of Assassins,
I knew how to handle guys like you.

115
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:35,320
Has Gideon figured out
the Pilgrim's next target yet?

116
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:37,520
{\an5}- That's peculiar.
- Peculiar or bad?

117
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:40,040
{\an5}Gideon, run another scan
for the whereabouts of the Pilgrim.

118
00:06:41,080 --> 00:06:42,080
<i>I'm sorry, sir.</i>

119
00:06:42,160 --> 00:06:44,240
<i>The timeline shows
no temporal distortions.</i>

120
00:06:44,320 --> 00:06:46,240
<i>I seem to be unable
to track the Pilgrim.</i>

121
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:47,480
That doesn't sound good.

122
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:48,960
No, it's quite the opposite.

123
00:06:49,640 --> 00:06:51,360
Without a way to track
the whereabouts of the Pilgrim,

124
00:06:51,440 --> 00:06:53,320
